                <note rend="inline" type="source">760j.67/68: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Secretary General of the League of Nations</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Drummond</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName> [<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1921-01-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                            notBefore="1921-01-22T00:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">undated</hi>
                        </date>].<lb/>[Received January 30, 1921—7 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Monsieur Da Cunha, Acting President of the Council of the League of Nations,
                    requests me to forward to you the following telegram: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Please thank President Wilson for his communication regarding Armenia
                            received by Monsieur Hymans on January 22nd.</p>
                        <p>I shall have the honor of submitting the views expressed therein for the
                            consideration of the Council at its next meeting. The note has been
                            brought to the knowledge of the representatives of the Principal Allied
                            Powers now meeting in Paris. The latter have announced that they will
                            shortly hold a conference on question relating to the Treaty of Sèvres.
                            Signed Da Cunha, Acting President of Council of League.[”]</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Drummond</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
